  <p><strong>Dependency rule:</strong> Dependencies flow downward only.</p>

  <h2>Domain Module Pattern</h2>

  <p>Each server domain in <code>packages/server/src/domains/</code> follows:</p>

  <pre><code>domains/[name]/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.ts     # Domain-specific types and enums
в”ңв”Җв”Җ repo.ts      # PostgreSQL queries (data access)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ service.ts   # Business logic (calls repo, triggers events)
в””в”Җв”Җ routes.ts    # Fastify route handlers (calls service)</code></pre>

  <h2>Core Data Model</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><code>flag_environments</code> is the <strong>core join</strong> &mdash; flags have no state without an environment</li>
    <li><code>gate_config</code> is JSONB for extensibility</li>
    <li>Group rules are JSONB arrays &mdash; rules within a group are ANDed, groups on a flag are ORed</li>
    <li>API keys store SHA-256 hash only; raw key shown once at creation</li>
    <li>Audit log stores before/after JSONB snapshots</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>API Response Envelope</h2>

  <pre><code>// Success
{"{"} data: T {"}"}

// List
{"{"} data: T[], cursor: string | null, has_more: boolean {"}"}

// Error
{"{"} error: {"{"} code: string, message: string {"}"} {"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Caching Strategy</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Cache Key</th><th>TTL</th><th>Invalidation</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>flick:env:{"{envId}"}:flags</code></td><td>60s</td><td>On any flag/group change in that env</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>flick:env:{"{envId}"}:flag:{"{key}"}</code></td><td>60s</td><td>On specific flag change</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>flick:apikey:{"{hash}"}</code></td><td>300s</td><td>On key revocation</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Write-through: miss &rarr; fetch from Postgres &rarr; write to Redis &rarr; return.</p>

  <h2>SDK Architecture</h2>

  <p>Both SDKs follow the same pattern:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Poll <code>GET /evaluate/config</code> with ETag for 304 support</li>
    <li>Cache full flag config in memory</li>
    <li>Evaluate locally (zero-latency) using shared evaluation logic</li>
    <li>Exponential backoff on failures, serve from cache during outages</li>
  </ol>
